hook.real_world_problem:
You've built an inventory CSV importer from Module 11. How do you test it?

```java
// The class you built:
class InventoryImporter {
    List<Product> importFromFile(Path csvFile) throws IOException {
        return Files.readAllLines(csvFile).stream()
            .skip(1)  // header
            .map(line -> parseProduct(line))
            .collect(Collectors.toList());
    }
}
```

**Naive approach:** create real files on disk, run test, manually clean up:
```java
@Test void importFromFile_validCsv_returns3Products() throws Exception {
    Files.writeString(Path.of("/tmp/test.csv"), "name,price\nMouse,799\nKeyboard,1999");
    // ...test...
    Files.delete(Path.of("/tmp/test.csv"));  // must clean up!
    // What if test fails mid-way? File stays forever!
}
```

**JUnit 5 way — @TempDir:**
```java
@Test
void importFromFile_validCsv_returns2Products(@TempDir Path tempDir) throws Exception {
    // JUnit creates a real temporary directory, auto-deleted after the test:
    Path csvFile = tempDir.resolve("products.csv");
    Files.writeString(csvFile, "name,price\nMouse,799\nKeyboard,1999\n");

    List<Product> products = importer.importFromFile(csvFile);

    assertEquals(2, products.size());
    assertEquals("Mouse", products.get(0).name());
}
// @TempDir directory is AUTOMATICALLY deleted after the test — even if it fails!
```

For HTTP clients — mock the HttpClient just like any other dependency. No real server needed.

concept_explanation.temp_dir:
**@TempDir — JUnit 5's built-in file sandbox:**

```java
import org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;
import java.nio.file.*;

class FileProcessorTest {

    // Option 1: inject per-test (different dir per test):
    @Test
    void readFile_validContent_parsesCorrectly(@TempDir Path tempDir) throws Exception {
        Path file = tempDir.resolve("data.txt");
        Files.writeString(file, "line1\nline2\nline3");
        // Use file in test...
    }  // tempDir auto-deleted here

    // Option 2: shared across all tests in class:
    @TempDir
    static Path sharedDir;  // static = shared; non-static = per-test

    @BeforeAll
    static void setUp() throws Exception {
        Files.writeString(sharedDir.resolve("shared.csv"), "data");
    }

    @Test
    void readFromSharedDir_works() throws Exception {
        Path file = sharedDir.resolve("shared.csv");
        assertTrue(Files.exists(file));
    }
}
```

**@TempDir guarantees:**
- Real temporary directory created by JUnit
- Unique per test (no collision between parallel tests)
- Automatically deleted after the test, even if it fails or throws

