@Test
void writeLine_appendsToExistingFile(@TempDir Path tempDir) throws Exception {
    Path logFile = tempDir.resolve('app.log');
    Files.writeString(logFile, 'first line\n');  // pre-existing content
    writer.writeLine(logFile, 'second line');
    List<String> lines = Files.readAllLines(logFile);
    assertEquals(2, lines.size());
    assertEquals('first line', lines.get(0));
    assertEquals('second line', lines.get(1));
}
```
@TempDir provides a clean directory. You write the initial content with Files.writeString, then call the method under test, then assert using Files.readAllLines.
